<h3>Main Colors</h3>
<p style="color: #00444A">
	When using color combinations the main D-CENT color must always be the dominant one. Keep the ratio at 80-20 or better, 90-10.
	<ul><h1 style="color:#00444A">The Header</h1>
	<h3 style="color: #007E84">Is Always Darker Than The Subheader</h3>
	</ul>
	When ratio for any reason is closer to 50/50, (eg. voting pie chart) use a lighter version of one, and a darker of the other.
	<span style="color: #FF69E8">Magenta combinations </span>are only for special highlights, like <span style="color: #9E2E8D">visited links,</span><span> rather than for general purpose content / material. </span><a href="">Unvisited links</a> should always be in the D-CENT color: #007E84 
</p>
